Name       : at
Arch       : i386
Version    : 3.1.8
Release    : 82.fc6
Size       : 77 k
Repo       : installed
Summary    : Job spooling tools.
License    : GPL
Description: At and batch read commands from standard input or from a specified
           : file. At allows you to specify that a command will be run at a
           : particular time. Batch will execute commands when the system load
           : levels drop to a particular level. Both commands use /bin/sh.
           : 
           : You should install the at package if you need a utility for
           : time-oriented job control. Note: If it is a recurring job that will
           : need to be repeated at the same time every day/week, etc. you
           : should use crontab instead.

